Source:  Autobiography
Author:  HEBERLEY
Vol / Page:  35
Edition:
Quote:   This is a piece of red wood with a nail driven through it and bent round in the shape of a hook commonly called a Barracoota hook [and used by whalers and Maoris for catching barracouta].
