Source:  BP Bishop Memoirs
Author:
Vol / Page:  Vol. IX No. 5 pp. 343-382) 360
Edition:
Quote:  The Moriori used wooden fishhooks but only for kahawai and manga (`barracouter' <i>Thyrsites atun</i>). The `barracouter' hook is a canoe-shaped bit of wood inlaid on the one side with a strip of bright shell of <i>Haliotis. </i>
Notes:  1928 Baucke Manuscript in Skinner and Baucke The Morioris (Bishop Museum Memoirs Vol. IX No. 5 pp. 343-382) 360

